Company Description                    




                        Puma Energy Zambia Plc engages in the marketing and distribution of petroleum products and lubricants in Zambia. The company operates in retail, commercial, industrial, lubricants, and aviation sectors. It owns approximately 53 service stations in Zambia. The company was formerly known as BP Zambia plc and changed its name to Puma Energy Zambia Plc in June 2011. Puma Energy Zambia Plc is based in Lusaka, Zambia. Puma Energy Zambia Plc is as a subsidiary of Puma Energy International B.V.                    


