Contact details

Zambia, LusakaPuma Energy Zambia PLC, Airtel House,Stand No 2375,Addis Ababa Drive,PO Box 31999,Lusaka, Zambia


Tel: +260 21 1 376100Fax: +260 21 1 376149

Email: Zambia@pumaenergy.com

Facebook:
facebook.com/PumaEnergyZambia











Date entered: 2011
Key market statistics:

Terminals: 2
Storage capacity: 21,500m³
Retail sites: 57
Airports: 3

As with all markets that we enter, Zambia is seeing a rapid growth of oil consumption. As such, we are successfully growing our B2B portfolios in Zambia by providing fuels, lubricants and other oil products to key clients in sectors such as mining and transportation. We are bolstering our provision of services to the aviation industry; we are a trusted supplier of avgas and jet fuel in Zambia. We also operate one of the largest privately owned oil products storage facilities in the country. Our two terminals provide a storage capacity of 21,500m³.
We have expanded our retail network and we currently have 57 retail sites.
Several Puma Energy Foundation projects were implemented in Zambia, including Alive and Kicking – a social entrepreneurial project for local women who helped stitch more than 4,000 footballs, which were then sold in Puma Energy service stations.
We educate our drivers in road safety; spread awareness through initiatives such as our road safety radio show in Zambia; support national road safety campaigns; and use the latest tracking technology to improve driver behaviour.




